67
00:17:05,641 --> 00:17:07,575
What are you doing here?

68
00:17:24,660 --> 00:17:27,561
- Cigarette?
- No, thanks.

69
00:17:41,977 --> 00:17:44,502
So... what are you doing here?

70
00:17:49,318 --> 00:17:51,752
I'm spending a few days meditating...

71
00:17:55,891 --> 00:17:57,882
In fact...

72
00:17:57,959 --> 00:17:59,893
I left my husband yesterday.

73
00:18:00,028 --> 00:18:02,588
I was married for almost ten years.

74
00:18:02,798 --> 00:18:06,734
And after giving it lots of thought
I made the decision...

75
00:18:06,802 --> 00:18:08,463
and here I am...

76
00:18:08,570 --> 00:18:10,470
You separated yesterday?

77
00:18:12,774 --> 00:18:14,401
Yes.

78
00:18:17,245 --> 00:18:18,837
But why?

79
00:18:20,849 --> 00:18:22,544
I don't know.

80
00:18:23,552 --> 00:18:26,248
We need to stop and think...
sometimes.

81
00:18:27,889 --> 00:18:31,723
Like when you wake up one morning
and something's bugging you...

82
00:18:31,927 --> 00:18:34,794
and that something is your partner.

83
00:18:34,963 --> 00:18:37,761
That's when you need
to stop and think...

84
00:18:42,337 --> 00:18:44,703
The tide's coming in,
shall we move back?

85
00:18:48,744 --> 00:18:51,736
A friend once said something
very wise.

86
00:18:52,347 --> 00:18:54,941
She compared Diego, her partner,

87
00:18:55,250 --> 00:18:57,946
to Nacho,
a guy she'd met somewhere...

88
00:18:58,053 --> 00:19:01,284
We shouldn't compare, but in this
case it's valid...

89
00:19:01,390 --> 00:19:03,551
She said:

90
00:19:03,759 --> 00:19:06,557
- Diego's fallen asleep in the armchair.
- Here?

91
00:19:06,628 --> 00:19:08,823
Yes... She thought:

92
00:19:09,765 --> 00:19:12,757
That idiot Diego's
fallen asleep in the armchair again.

93
00:19:13,268 --> 00:19:17,227
But then Nacho falls asleep in the
same armchair,

94
00:19:17,906 --> 00:19:21,740
and she thinks: How cute Nacho looks
asleep in the armchair...

95
00:19:21,877 --> 00:19:23,538
That's how it is.

96
00:19:25,514 --> 00:19:30,451
Perhaps your friend was a bore and
the guys just fell asleep.

97
00:19:30,886 --> 00:19:35,653
No. I'm not saying it's always
the way but...

98
00:19:36,458 --> 00:19:39,655
some partners are for life
but others aren't.

99
00:19:39,961 --> 00:19:41,929
We just need to realize in time.

100
00:19:43,999 --> 00:19:46,467
Well, perhaps you realized in time.

101
00:19:47,803 --> 00:19:50,271
I don't know. I'm not sure...

102
00:19:50,372 --> 00:19:51,964
- No?
- No...

103
00:19:54,543 --> 00:19:57,603
- Are you married?
- Yes.

104
00:19:59,514 --> 00:20:02,347
Actually my wife will be waiting
for me in the hotel.

105
00:20:02,451 --> 00:20:06,285
Really? Go back, then.
She must be worried.

106
00:20:06,455 --> 00:20:07,854
I don't think so...

107
00:20:08,323 --> 00:20:11,486
- No?
- No...

108
00:20:14,663 --> 00:20:17,564
- Have you got kids?
- No.

109
00:20:18,033 --> 00:20:21,833
- Sorry, I was curious.
- That's fine. I didn't want kids.

110
00:20:22,571 --> 00:20:24,300
Why?

111
00:20:24,840 --> 00:20:26,501
Because...

112
00:20:27,676 --> 00:20:29,769
I'll tell you in a minute.
Do you know what?

113
00:20:30,612 --> 00:20:33,445
I left my phone in the bar
where I had lunch...

114
00:20:33,715 --> 00:20:36,445
It's near here. Can I ask you
to watch my stuff,

115
00:20:36,518 --> 00:20:38,509
- and I'll be back in five minutes...
- I'll go with you.

116
00:20:38,920 --> 00:20:40,888
There's no need. I'll leave my bag
with you and I'll be right back.

117
00:20:40,989 --> 00:20:45,323
- I want to go with you.
- I'll leave my things here.

118
00:20:45,594 --> 00:20:47,619
- And if you don't come back?
- I'll be back.

119
00:20:47,762 --> 00:20:49,457
I'm coming with you.

120
00:20:53,068 --> 00:20:55,730
It's not like I didn't want kids.

121
00:20:56,438 --> 00:21:01,637
At first I just wanted to enjoy
being with my partner.

122
00:21:02,511 --> 00:21:05,742
Then I started working hard...

123
00:21:06,414 --> 00:21:08,882
and couldn't find the right time.

124
00:21:09,451 --> 00:21:13,478
Then when I stopped
looking for excuses,

125
00:21:13,989 --> 00:21:18,426
I realized I couldn't imagine Juan
as the father of my kids.

126
00:21:19,461 --> 00:21:22,453
It's strange because I reckon
he'd be an excellent father,

127
00:21:23,465 --> 00:21:25,695
but I just didn't want
kids with him.

128
00:21:25,800 --> 00:21:29,634
And in that process
you went through,

129
00:21:29,871 --> 00:21:34,638
did you imagine any particular
father for your children?

130
00:21:39,014 --> 00:21:40,743
- No.
- No?

131
00:21:41,716 --> 00:21:43,581
But I should start trying
to imagine it,

132
00:21:43,685 --> 00:21:47,451
because I don't have so many years
left for existential matters...

133
00:21:47,956 --> 00:21:52,723
You do... four, five...

134
00:22:00,368 --> 00:22:02,393
- And you?
- What?

135
00:22:03,338 --> 00:22:04,828
Have you got kids?

136
00:22:05,974 --> 00:22:07,601
One daughter...

137
00:22:07,976 --> 00:22:10,638
How odd.
I could never see you as a father.

138
00:22:13,982 --> 00:22:17,782
- What's he playing?
- I don't know...

139
00:22:48,883 --> 00:22:50,817
Shall we go?

140
00:23:00,295 --> 00:23:02,559
So why could you never see me
as a father?

141
00:23:03,865 --> 00:23:05,560
I don't know.

142
00:23:07,602 --> 00:23:10,594
- How old is she?
- Six.

143
00:23:11,006 --> 00:23:15,409
Agustina's her name. She's staying
with her grandparents...

144
00:23:15,577 --> 00:23:17,568
Are you happy with your wife?

145
00:23:24,419 --> 00:23:26,853
Am I happy with my wife?

146
00:23:42,837 --> 00:23:44,634
- I don't know.
- No?

147
00:23:44,739 --> 00:23:47,503
No, no.

148
00:23:49,544 --> 00:23:52,809
We've been together for a long time,
and have many things in common...

149
00:23:55,750 --> 00:23:57,513
But I don't know...

150
00:24:00,288 --> 00:24:04,349
When I wake up in the morning and
see her beside me in bed,

151
00:24:05,393 --> 00:24:09,796
I'm neither happy nor sad...

152
00:24:09,898 --> 00:24:11,627
You haven't answered my question.

153
00:24:27,615 --> 00:24:31,415
Do you think there is a
precise moment in time...

154
00:24:31,686 --> 00:24:35,782
when you can say:
From now on...

155
00:24:36,491 --> 00:24:41,360
I don't love that woman and I don't
enjoy doing what I used to with her.

156
00:24:42,630 --> 00:24:43,790
I don't think so.

157
00:24:43,898 --> 00:24:48,801
I don't mean a precise moment
of infidelity.

158
00:24:48,870 --> 00:24:50,861
No, it's a bit like what
you were just saying.

159
00:24:51,072 --> 00:24:53,905
Life follows its course,

160
00:24:57,779 --> 00:24:59,007
and one day you realize...

161
00:24:59,547 --> 00:25:04,348
that what you liked
about the woman you loved,

162
00:25:05,553 --> 00:25:09,182
are the things that most annoy you
or bother you...

163
00:25:13,461 --> 00:25:14,894
Shall we go on?

164
00:25:17,332 --> 00:25:20,893
It's a little like what happens
with your eyesight.

165
00:25:21,002 --> 00:25:24,768
It hasn't happened to me but people
say that one day you begin...

166
00:25:24,939 --> 00:25:28,306
to lose your eyesight, right?

167
00:25:28,943 --> 00:25:33,676
They say that happens
at a precise moment in time.

168
00:25:33,848 --> 00:25:37,944
You go to a restaurant,
they give you a menu,

169
00:25:39,687 --> 00:25:43,589
but you have to move it around
in order to see it properly, right?

170
00:25:43,658 --> 00:25:46,252
If somebody could tell you when...

171
00:25:46,361 --> 00:25:49,330
I'm serious. What's so funny?

172
00:25:50,265 --> 00:25:51,857
It's...

173
00:25:52,333 --> 00:25:54,961
I'm laughing because I've just
remembered something daft,

174
00:25:55,303 --> 00:25:58,431
- shall I tell you?
- OK.

175
00:25:59,741 --> 00:26:04,235
Not long ago my ex started wearing
glasses but couldn't accept it.

176
00:26:04,345 --> 00:26:08,714
So I could be sitting at home
reading or something,

177
00:26:09,384 --> 00:26:13,411
and I'd hear in the background:
"Where the hell did I leave my glasses?"

178
00:26:13,521 --> 00:26:17,480
It was his sort of stock phrase...

179
00:26:18,293 --> 00:26:20,955
I'll be there soon... honest.

180
00:26:26,367 --> 00:26:28,767
Go on, I interrupted you.
What were you saying?

181
00:26:30,338 --> 00:26:31,999
Where was I?

182
00:26:32,774 --> 00:26:34,708
Oh, yes.

183
00:26:35,944 --> 00:26:39,812
We all think that at one magical
moment you'll fall in love,

184
00:26:39,948 --> 00:26:42,883
and you'll want to spend all
your life with that person.

185
00:26:43,051 --> 00:26:46,487
What I wanted to know was:

186
00:26:46,588 --> 00:26:48,647
Is there also an exact moment...

187
00:26:48,890 --> 00:26:53,224
when that stops for ever?

188
00:26:56,865 --> 00:26:58,833
It's as if...

189
00:26:59,000 --> 00:27:02,731
the relationship crashes,
or you crash...

190
00:27:06,674 --> 00:27:08,801
Like a crash... let me think
about that...

191
00:27:08,910 --> 00:27:12,641
Alright, a crash,
but my question is:

192
00:27:14,315 --> 00:27:18,411
Do you crash one day and find that
everything bugs you about them,

193
00:27:18,786 --> 00:27:23,917
or do you crash the day you realize
there are many things that bug you?

194
00:27:25,326 --> 00:27:27,692
- It's very complicated.
- It is.

195
00:27:27,795 --> 00:27:29,524
This is it.

196
00:27:31,633 --> 00:27:34,625
- Will you wait?
- Of course.

197
00:27:35,737 --> 00:27:37,500
I'll be right back.

198
00:28:29,958 --> 00:28:32,169
That's lucky.
You weren't very hopeful.

199
00:28:32,170 --> 00:28:33,225
I was...

200
00:28:34,495 --> 00:28:36,326
OK, where were we?

201
00:28:37,598 --> 00:28:40,624
According to you we were
busy crashing.

202
00:28:43,471 --> 00:28:45,701
You could also ask yourself,

203
00:28:46,374 --> 00:28:49,775
not only if it's a process or if
there's a moment of rupture,

204
00:28:49,877 --> 00:28:51,902
but you could also ask...

205
00:28:52,647 --> 00:28:54,808
if you were ever really happy
with that person,

206
00:28:54,949 --> 00:28:58,783
or if life simply brought
you together. Don't you think?

207
00:28:59,454 --> 00:29:03,220
- Yes, that's different, isn't it?
- Yes...

208
00:29:03,858 --> 00:29:05,792
but doesn't it scare you
to think it?

209
00:29:12,900 --> 00:29:17,337
I don't know... I don't know...

210
00:29:22,410 --> 00:29:25,470
The fact is I don't stop
to think very often.

211
00:29:25,546 --> 00:29:27,605
I don't have the time...

212
00:29:29,884 --> 00:29:32,853
Life is what happens and
I get carried along...

213
00:29:36,357 --> 00:29:38,518
At times I feel very tired...

214
00:29:38,960 --> 00:29:40,825
You're in a bad way...

215
00:29:47,802 --> 00:29:51,898
- Shall we go?
- Yes.

216
00:30:00,314 --> 00:30:02,680
I'd imagined so many chance meetings
with you,

217
00:30:03,651 --> 00:30:06,449
but never like this.

218
00:30:07,655 --> 00:30:09,816
How then?
With you swearing a lot at me?

219
00:30:10,591 --> 00:30:12,252
Yes, a lot.

220
00:30:15,863 --> 00:30:17,728
This is a short cut...

221
00:30:19,367 --> 00:30:21,392
- I dreamt about you several times...
- Oh, yes?

222
00:30:21,502 --> 00:30:23,265
Yes, several...

223
00:30:24,539 --> 00:30:28,339
In one particular dream...
shall I tell you?

224
00:30:28,409 --> 00:30:29,671
Go on.

225
00:30:30,978 --> 00:30:35,642
I was trying to contact you
by phone,

226
00:30:37,652 --> 00:30:42,419
and as I dialed your number
the phone disintegrated.

227
00:30:43,491 --> 00:30:47,757
And there was an elderly woman
helping me,

228
00:30:47,862 --> 00:30:51,628
by bringing the missing keys
I needed to dial your number.

229
00:30:52,433 --> 00:30:54,560
